issue.title: Compiled binary is too big
issue.body:
- Robotgo version (or commit ref): fdaa440f26
- Go version: 1.15.3
- Gcc version: 9.2.0
- Operating system and bit: Windows 10 64 bit
- Resolution: 1920x1080
- Can you reproduce the bug at [Examples](https://github.com/go-vgo/robotgo/blob/master/examples/main.go):
  - [ ] Yes (provide example code)
  - [ ] No
  - [X ] Not relevant
- Provide example code:

```Go
package main

import "github.com/go-vgo/robotgo"

func main() {
	robotgo.TypeStr("Hello World!", 1.0)
}
```
- Log gist:

## Description

Compiling the above code with `go build -ldflags "-s -w"` produces a 4.1 MB binary. The corresponding code using [enigo](https://github.com/enigo-rs/enigo) in Rust produces a 244 kB binary. Since both are statically linked, I think that the comparison is fair. For reference, a calculator written in Go and Tk weighs 2.4 MB.

issue.title: Error with Go version 1.19 in windows
issue.body:
I'm trying to compile the project, but i'm getting errors like: 

`go get  github.com/go-vgo/robotgo@latest`

And i got 

```
go: go.mod file not found in current directory or any parent directory.
        'go get' is no longer supported outside a module.
        To build and install a command, use 'go install' with a version,
        like 'go install example.com/cmd@latest'
        For more information, see https://golang.org/doc/go-get-install-deprecation
        or run 'go help get' or 'go help install'.
```

If i try to use install 

`go install  github.com/go-vgo/robotgo@latest
`

And again

```

go: downloading github.com/go-vgo/robotgo v0.100.10
go: downloading github.com/vcaesar/keycode v0.10.0
go: downloading github.com/lxn/win v0.0.0-20210218163916-a377121e959e
go: downloading github.com/robotn/gohook v0.31.3
go: downloading github.com/vcaesar/tt v0.20.0
go: downloading github.com/vcaesar/imgo v0.30.0
go: downloading github.com/vcaesar/gops v0.21.3
go: downloading github.com/shirou/gopsutil v3.21.10+incompatible
go: downloading golang.org/x/image v0.0.0-20211028202545-6944b10bf410
go: downloading golang.org/x/sys v0.0.0-20211123173158-ef496fb156ab
go: downloading github.com/StackExchange/wmi v1.2.1
go: downloading github.com/go-ole/go-ole v1.2.6
**package github.com/go-vgo/robotgo is not a main package**
```

It seem that Go deprecated the Get command and i think that install search for i file that is not there

PD: i'm not want to work direct with GO, i was trying to install robotn and i got the same errors that i describe before, so i switch to the commend line in GO

issue.title: Error with Go version 1.19 in windows
issue.body:
I'm trying to compile the project, but i'm getting errors like: 

`go get  github.com/go-vgo/robotgo@latest`

And i got 

```
go: go.mod file not found in current directory or any parent directory.
        'go get' is no longer supported outside a module.
        To build and install a command, use 'go install' with a version,
        like 'go install example.com/cmd@latest'
        For more information, see https://golang.org/doc/go-get-install-deprecation
        or run 'go help get' or 'go help install'.
```

If i try to use install 

`go install  github.com/go-vgo/robotgo@latest
`

And again

```

go: downloading github.com/go-vgo/robotgo v0.100.10
go: downloading github.com/vcaesar/keycode v0.10.0
go: downloading github.com/lxn/win v0.0.0-20210218163916-a377121e959e
go: downloading github.com/robotn/gohook v0.31.3
go: downloading github.com/vcaesar/tt v0.20.0
go: downloading github.com/vcaesar/imgo v0.30.0
go: downloading github.com/vcaesar/gops v0.21.3
go: downloading github.com/shirou/gopsutil v3.21.10+incompatible
go: downloading golang.org/x/image v0.0.0-20211028202545-6944b10bf410
go: downloading golang.org/x/sys v0.0.0-20211123173158-ef496fb156ab
go: downloading github.com/StackExchange/wmi v1.2.1
go: downloading github.com/go-ole/go-ole v1.2.6
**package github.com/go-vgo/robotgo is not a main package**
```

It seem that Go deprecated the Get command and i think that install search for i file that is not there

PD: i'm not want to work direct with GO, i was trying to install robotn and i got the same errors that i describe before, so i switch to the commend line in GO
